description:
&lt;p&gt;The Renal Department at Lancashire Teaching Hospital NHS Trust are looking for an enthusiastic and flexible person looking for a challenge in a post that is both interesting and varied. We are looking for a person with excellent administrative skills who is a team player with a flexible approach to working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require a well organised person to co-ordinate the changing requirements of home dialysis patients in respect of their dialysis prescriptions and consumables as well as providing effective support and co-ordination of home dialysis and holiday dialysis. You should ideally possess excellent communication skills and have experience of entering data. Good organisational and communication skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post supports the Home Therapy Manager and therefore administrative experience and a typing speed of 50wpm is desirable. Knowledge of a hospital working environment and medical terminology would be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: Week commencing 23rd November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquiries about the post or to arrange a visit to the department contact Joanne Roper, Clinical Support Manager on 01772 528146.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJoanne RoperJob titleClinical Support Manager, RenalEmail addressjoanne.roper@lthtr.nhs.ukTelephone number01772 528146&lt;/p&gt;
